// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p09/fail.test — P9 mismatched conditional fail-
// cases per `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` notes section + the FR-037
// locked-string table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`
// + tasks.md T045.
//
// P9 has TWO violatable rules, both with FR-037-locked message
// strings. We exercise BOTH in this one fixture using
// FileCheck's `--check-prefix`:
//
//   FR-037 P9 lock #1:
//     `'#endif' without matching '#if' / '#ifdef' / '#ifndef'`
//   FR-037 P9 lock #2:
//     `unterminated #if at end of file`
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII the failing fixture asserts the
// EXACT diagnostic strings. Renaming or weakening either later
// requires a contract amendment in
// `contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md` PLUS this fixture's
// update in the same change.
//
// **RED state**: the unchanged Phase-3 tree's lexer tokenizes the
// conditional directives literally and exits 0; no preprocessor
// exists to detect the mismatch. Phase-4's conditional stack
// raises both diagnostics.

// ---- CASE 1: extra #endif (no matching opener) ---------------------
// Just a stray `#endif` with no preceding `#if`/`#ifdef`/`#ifndef`.
//
// RUN: echo '#endif' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=EXTRA

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING #1 — exact match:
// EXTRA: error: '#endif' without matching '#if' / '#ifdef' / '#ifndef'

// ---- CASE 2: unterminated #if at EOF -------------------------------
// `#if 1` opens a region that's never closed.
//
// RUN: echo '#if 1'      >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'never_seen' >> %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=UNTERM

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING #2 — exact match:
// UNTERM: error: unterminated #if at end of file
